d decided to set out and see the world. Thus Huitzil had roamed the land, seeking new knowledge, experiences and friends. If by chance you meet this guy and asked him, “What class are you?” and he’ll reply with a grin, “I’m a pintsized demigod, fear my nuking power.” After much pain and sorrow, Huitzil had finally learned enough in his travels to be considered a low level channeler of the mystic arts. If chance allows that he be invited into a group, he prefers most the company of a warrior, a rogue, a cleric, a bard and an enchanter. Out of all the classes Huitzil has ever met, there is nothing he admired more than clerics who with the blessing of their gods are able to bring him back from death – which has occurred too many times for his taste.  Huitzil has vowed death to all giants out there that has tried to squish him more often than not and since he has similar goals as that of Coldain; he became one of the few outlanders they trusted. Huitzil has been to a few guilds trying to find the one that’s for him but no success as of yet. He has heard of the Guild of Vengeful Dragons and thought, “Can this be the guild I’ve been searching for? To finally be among equals, to meet new friends, to be able to group with people he can trust to guard his life; I have to take this window of opportunity.” <br>
